A taxi driver was sentenced to five years in jail for culpable homicide yesterday after the illegal taxi he was driving collided with an SA Breweries truck, killing nine people and injuring 13.  The Komani Magistrate’s Court found Whittlesea driver Simphiwe Qwebani, 44, guilty of nine counts of culpable homicide for the May 10 2013 accident. According to the evidence given in court, Qwebani was driving a Mercedes Sprinter, transporting people from Whittlesea to Mthwakazi village. On the R351 between Sada and Whittlesea, Qwebani hit the SAB truck from the back, resulting in the death of nine passengers. His wife cried uncontrollably yesterday when he was taken to the holding cells. For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions. The truck driver who crashed into four taxis and a car killing 22 people is expected to appear in the Pinetown Magistrate's Court on Monday. Sanele Goodness May, 23, from Swaziland, was arrested on September 6 on 22 counts of murder and one of reckless or negligent driving. Magistrate Wendolynn… September 16, 2013 In "News" Four teachers were killed in a freak accident yesterday when the taxi in which they were travelling collided with the blade of a bulldozer being transported on the back of truck. Part of the blade, extending out past the side of the trailer carrying the bulldozer, ripped through the side… March 5, 2015 In "News" At least nine people were killed when a minibus taxi collided head on with a truck on the R63 between Komga and Bisho this  afternoon. The driver of the taxi and that of the truck are among those who died at the scene. Eastern Cape health spokesman Sizwe Kupelo said two… March 5, 2017 In "News"